**OWASP A05: Security Misconfiguration**

Without explicit CORS configuration, the default Express behavior blocks cross-origin requests — but this is **implicit**, not explicit. If any middleware (or a future developer) adds `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *`, the `/users` endpoint will leak PII (emails) to any origin.

